Reference-contexts: INEL is developing a Waste Assay Measurement Integration System (WAMIS) to improve confidence in and lower the uncertainty of waste characterization data <ref> (Mousseau 2 et al. 1995) </ref>. WAMIS will consist of two major components - a data access/visualization component and a data interpretation component. <p> WAMIS will consist of two major components - a data access/visualization component and a data interpretation component. The WAMIS data interpretation component will make use of artificial intelligence (AI) techniques to determine waste matrix and source material characteristics and the relationships among them to derive improved assays <ref> (Mousseau et al. 1995) </ref>. The system will act as an expert in the domain of nuclear waste characterization that can bring a wide variety of information to bear to determine the reliability of a characterization produced by a nondestructive analysis/nondestructive examination (NDA/NDE) assay system (or set of assay systems).
